      <h1>Cari and Mom Las Vegas Getaway</h1>
      <p>
        This page pulls together the full trip plan for Cari and her mother:
        Sphere, Cirque du Soleil, Old Vegas, Mon Ami Gabi brunch, spa ideas,
        and extra experiences. The layout is built for quick reference on a phone
        while you are in town.
      </p>

      <div class="tag-row">
        <div class="tag">Late mornings</div>
        <div class="tag">Wine and ambience</div>
        <div class="tag">Sightseeing and shows</div>
        <div class="tag">Unique shopping</div>
        <div class="tag">Neon and Old Vegas</div>
      </div>

      <h2>Trip snapshot</h2>
      <p>
        Hotel: Club Wyndham Grand Desert, just off the Strip. This keeps nights
        quiet but makes rideshare to the Strip and downtown fast and inexpensive.
      </p>
      <p>
        Core anchors:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Postcard from Earth at the Sphere</li>
        <li>O by Cirque du Soleil at Bellagio</li>
        <li>Mad Apple by Cirque du Soleil at New York New York</li>
        <li>Old Vegas and Fremont Street</li>
        <li>Farewell brunch at Mon Ami Gabi with Bellagio fountain views</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How to use this site</h2>
      <p>
        1. Open the Daily itinerary tab for a day by day run through with timing and why each choice was made.
      </p>
      <p>
        2. Open Tickets and showtimes for where to buy seats, pricing strategy, and alternative showtimes.
      </p>
      <p>
        3. Open Brunch and dining for Mon Ami Gabi, backup brunch spots, and what to order.
      </p>
      <p>
        4. Open Spa deals for realistic discounted spa ideas that still feel nice.
      </p>
      <p>
        5. Open Neon Museum and maps to see where the Neon Museum fits relative to Old Vegas and the Strip.
      </p>
      <p>
        6. Open Unique add ons for extra experiences if they have energy and want more memories.
      </p>
