    <section id="itinerary" class="section">
      <h2>Daily itinerary</h2>
      <p>
        Times are approximate. The idea is smooth flow and built in breathing room,
        not a forced schedule. Tap a day to expand or collapse it.
      </p>

      <!-- Day 1 -->
      <div class="day-card">
        <div class="day-header">
          <div class="day-header-main">
            <div class="day-title">Day 1 ‚Äî Arrival and Sphere night</div>
            <div class="day-subtitle">Arrive, settle in, wine, Sphere, early finish</div>
          </div>
          <div class="day-toggle">‚ñæ</div>
        </div>
        <div class="day-body open">
          <div class="slot">
            <div class="time">3:00 pm to 4:30 pm</div>
            <div class="title">Arrive and check in at Club Wyndham Grand Desert</div>
            <div class="why">
              Drop bags, freshen up, and get a feel for the property. Being just off-strip
              keeps the room quiet while still being a short rideshare away from everything.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="slot">
            <div class="time">5:30 pm</div>
            <div class="title">Head toward Resorts World and the Sphere area</div>
            <div class="why">
              Rideshare to Resorts World. This gives them a relaxed lead-in to the evening,
              and puts them close to the Sphere without rushing.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="slot">
            <div class="time">6:00 pm to 7:15 pm</div>
            <div class="title">Wine and small plates at Wally‚Äôs, Resorts World</div>
            <div class="why">
              Wally‚Äôs is built around wine, charcuterie, and upscale bites, in a lively but
              not overwhelming room. It is ideal for a wine loving mother and daughter pair
              before the biggest visual show in town.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="slot">
            <div class="time">7:30 pm to about 9:15 pm</div>
            <div class="title">Postcard from Earth at the Sphere</div>
            <div class="why">
              This is the most uniquely modern Vegas experience. The screen surrounds you,
              the sound is immersive, and the seats can include haptics. Seeing it on the
              first night sets the tone for the whole trip.
            </div>
            <div class="pill-row small">
              <div class="pill">Typical options: afternoon, early evening, late evening</div>
              <div class="pill">Aim for a 7:00 pm show for this flow</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="slot">
            <div class="time">After the show</div>
            <div class="title">Light walk and back to the hotel</div>
            <div class="why">
              They can stroll a bit through an attached resort, then grab a quick rideshare
              back to the Grand Desert. Night one stays magical but not exhausting.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Day 2 -->
      <div class="day-card">
        <div class="day-header">
          <div class="day-header-main">
            <div class="day-title">Day 2 ‚Äî Arts District, Neon and O</div>
            <div class="day-subtitle">Unique shops, optional Neon Museum, chef dinner, Cirque</div>
          </div>
          <div class="day-toggle">‚ñæ</div>
        </div>
        <div class="day-body">
          <div class="slot">
            <div class="time">Late morning, around 11:00 am</div>
            <div class="title">Arts District, Main Street and Antique Alley</div>
            <div class="why">
              This is the opposite of luxury malls. Independent vintage shops, local makers,
              art, and one of a kind finds. They can browse slowly, grab a coffee, and pick
              up gifts that feel personal.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="slot">
            <div class="time">Early afternoon</div>
            <div class="title">Optional Neon Museum stop</div>
            <div class="why">
              From the Arts District the Neon Museum is only a short hop. They can
              walk the outdoor boneyard among classic Las Vegas signs and choose between
              a daytime visit for clearer detail or a nighttime visit for glowing neon.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="slot">
            <div class="time">Mid afternoon</div>
            <div class="title">Reset at the hotel</div>
            <div class="why">
              Back to the Wyndham for rest, showers, and getting ready. Tonight is the
              most elegant night, so they should have time to prepare at an easy pace.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="slot">
            <div class="time">Evening</div>
            <div class="title">Chef driven dinner and O at Bellagio</div>
            <div class="why">
              They start with a special dinner at Bellagio or nearby, paired with wine,
              then walk into O, which is the most romantic and visually beautiful Cirque
              show in town with a water stage and world class acrobatics.
            </div>
            <div class="pill-row small">
              <div class="pill">Early show flow: dinner around 4:30 to 5:00, O at 6:30</div>
              <div class="pill">Late show flow: dinner around 6:00, O at 9:00</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Day 3 -->
      <div class="day-card">
        <div class="day-header">
          <div class="day-header-main">
            <div class="day-title">Day 3 ‚Äî Fergusons, Container Park, Old Vegas, Mad Apple</div>
            <div class="day-subtitle">Local shops, Fremont, happy hour, high energy Cirque</div>
          </div>
          <div class="day-toggle">‚ñæ</div>
        </div>
        <div class="day-body">
          <div class="slot">
            <div class="time">Late morning</div>
            <div class="title">Fergusons Downtown</div>
            <div class="why">
              A small community block centered on local makers and small boutiques. Good
              for jewelry, home goods, clothing, and coffee in a relaxed setting.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="slot">
            <div class="time">Midday</div>
            <div class="title">Downtown Container Park</div>
            <div class="why">
              Shipping containers turned into quirky shops and eateries. Quick to walk,
              great for photos, and easy to pair with Fremont.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="slot">
            <div class="time">Afternoon</div>
            <div class="title">Fremont Street and Old Vegas</div>
            <div class="why">
              Classic Vegas lights, live entertainment, older casinos, and strong people watching.
              This is the energetic, neon soaked part of the trip.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="slot">
            <div class="time">Late afternoon</div>
            <div class="title">Return to hotel and refresh</div>
            <div class="why">
              They recharge before a social evening built around cocktails and a show.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="slot">
            <div class="time">Early evening</div>
            <div class="title">Happy hour and small plates</div>
            <div class="why">
              A stylish bar or restaurant lounge gives them cocktails, wine, and bites
              without a heavy, sit forever meal before a late show.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="slot">
            <div class="time">Night</div>
            <div class="title">Mad Apple at New York New York</div>
            <div class="why">
              Mad Apple is loud, funny, and very modern. It feels like New York nightlife
              reimagined as a Cirque show with music, comedy, and acrobatics.
            </div>
            <div class="pill-row small">
              <div class="pill">Early show option: 7:00 pm</div>
              <div class="pill">Late show option: 9:30 pm (fits best with a longer happy hour)</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Day 4 -->
      <div class="day-card">
        <div class="day-header">
